                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Kindly ask your son to take<lb/> the text of my prayer in the Senate yesterday<lb/> from the New York Sun.&#45;&#45;altering<lb/></p> 
            <p>1. in it&#44; in line 2&#44; &#34;on this earth&#44;&#34; into &#34;in this<lb/> world which Thou has created according to<lb/> Thy will&#34; &#40;N. D. This is our Kaddish of course&#41;.<lb/>
                2. Change in last paragraph &#34;<hi rend="underline">They</hi> are one<lb/> into &#34;<hi rend="underline">Thou</hi> art one.&#34;<lb/>
                3. On 5th line from end of prayer&#44; take out<lb/> the words &#34;and of&#44;&#34;&#45;&#45;putting instead a comma<lb/> after &#34;Union.&#34;<lb/>
                Kindly omit <hi rend="underline">all</hi> the Series remarks as to<lb/> my personal appearance.<lb/></p>
            <p>Yrs with regards<lb/>
                H Pereira Mendes.<lb/></p>
            <p>I went to the Cooper last Sat&#39;d night &#38;<lb/> Sunday aft&#39;noon.  When you come&#44; let us<lb/> know.  <hi rend="underline">Dinner Sundays 1.30.pm</hi><lb/></p>
            
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>The Phila. Press report of my<lb/> prayer does not contain all&#45;&#45;the<lb/> N. Y. Sun&#39;s complete.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
